$BR$BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD 
$BR
The function \(h(z)= \frac {1-2 \cdot z} {z^2-z-6} = \frac {1-2 \cdot z} {(z+2)(z-3)}\) is discontinuous at \(z=-2\) and \(z=3\), at which there are infinite discontinuities.
